All Implemented Interfaces:
BoundedMap<K,V>, Serializable, Cloneable, Map<K,V>
public final class FIFOMap<K,V>
extends LinkedHashMap<K,V>
implements BoundedMap<K,V>

A LinkedHashMap implementation of BoundedMap which removes stale mappings in insertion/first-in-first-out order.

This implementation is not thread-safe. If multiple threads modify this map concurrently it must be synchronized externally, consider "wrapping" the map using the Collections3.synchronizedBoundedMap(BoundedMap) method.

Author:
Zhenya Leonov

putAll

public void putAll(Map<? extends K,? extends V> m)
Copies all of the mappings from the specified map to this map, removing stale entries (according to their insertion order) as necessary to prevent the map from exceeding its capacity. The effect of this call is equivalent to that of calling put(K, V) on this map once for each mapping in the specified map.
